@andyfeller In `issue/create`, non-interactive and non-editor modes are equivalent to `titleProvided && bodyProvided == true`. In `pr/create`, when `titleProvided && bodyProvided` is true, it won't enter this `else` block, which doesn't check if the title is provided. Instead, it will enter the block at [line 336-342](https://github.com/cli/cli/blob/e18c00228314340509ec0c56f15a992a2950ba09/pkg/cmd/pr/create/create.go#L336-L342), where the presence of a title is already ensured.
https://github.com/cli/cli/blob/e18c00228314340509ec0c56f15a992a2950ba09/pkg/cmd/pr/create/create.go#L379-L416
Therefore, the existence of a title can be ensured in all scenarios: interactive mode, editor mode, and non-interactive mode+non-editor mode (`titleProvided && bodyProvided == true`).
